The paper discusses the consensus protocols used in blockchain networks, which involves distributed computing, fault tolerance, and network security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
